WEBVTT

00:20.800 --> 00:25.820
The Happy Holiday Hotel is a small English

00:25.820 --> 00:27.520
hotel near the sea.

00:27.520 --> 00:30.720
These people work there.

00:32.140 --> 00:34.760
George, the hotel manager.

00:35.940 --> 00:38.620
Mary, she helps George.

00:39.760 --> 00:41.720
George and Mary are married.

00:43.120 --> 00:45.200
Judy, the cook.

00:47.280 --> 00:48.920
Peter, an old man.

00:49.820 --> 00:52.660
He helps outside in the garden and carries

00:52.660 --> 00:54.000
the bags in the hotel.

00:54.000 --> 00:54.180
Tell.

01:10.460 --> 01:13.480
Scene 1, the telephone call.

01:15.200 --> 01:18.520
In the Happy Holiday Hotel, it is three

01:18.520 --> 01:18.980
o'clock.

01:19.940 --> 01:21.880
George is talking to Mary.

01:21.880 --> 01:24.400
The telephone rings.

01:30.020 --> 01:33.340
Hello. Happy Holiday Hotel.

01:34.400 --> 01:35.520
George Harris here.

01:36.720 --> 01:39.300
Yes, I am the manager.

01:40.320 --> 01:41.840
Tony, who?

01:42.800 --> 01:46.500
Oh, Tony Maddock, the TV star.

01:47.480 --> 01:49.620
Your Tony Maddock's secretary.

01:50.540 --> 01:51.640
I see.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.540
Yes, that's fine.

01:55.540 --> 01:59.140
You want a large room for Tony and

01:59.140 --> 02:00.740
he wants to see the sea.

02:01.440 --> 02:01.700
Right?

02:02.640 --> 02:05.560
Yes, yes, I know.

02:06.120 --> 02:07.680
Tony is very important.

02:08.700 --> 02:09.940
A TV star.

02:11.380 --> 02:14.420
Yes, fish, you say?

02:15.260 --> 02:17.180
Yes, that's easy.

02:17.180 --> 02:19.460
Right then.

02:20.120 --> 02:24.320
Today, Tony's coming today.

02:25.180 --> 02:26.340
Fine.

02:27.060 --> 02:29.280
Goodbye and thank you.

02:31.280 --> 02:34.140
George puts down the telephone.

02:35.320 --> 02:39.520
Today, Tony's coming today.

02:40.220 --> 02:43.820
Mary, listen, I've got good news.

02:43.820 --> 02:46.640
Don't shout, George.

02:47.580 --> 02:48.200
What is it?

02:48.640 --> 02:49.980
Tony Maddock.

02:50.420 --> 02:54.820
You know, the television star is coming to

02:54.820 --> 02:56.740
our hotel this afternoon.

02:57.280 --> 03:00.620
Oh, Tony Maddock.

03:01.100 --> 03:02.180
He's famous.

03:02.980 --> 03:06.160
He's coming here at five o'clock today.

03:07.000 --> 03:09.780
He's a TV star, you say?

03:10.680 --> 03:12.500
Is he in Neighbors?

03:13.340 --> 03:15.440
I don't watch TV very much.

03:15.920 --> 03:16.700
Neighbors?

03:17.820 --> 03:18.620
Probably.

03:19.620 --> 03:22.600
He's going to have our best room and

03:22.600 --> 03:23.720
our best food.

03:24.660 --> 03:26.840
I'm going to look at the room now.

03:27.580 --> 03:30.420
Fine, George, but I'm busy.

03:31.000 --> 03:32.200
I'm going to the supermarket.

03:33.060 --> 03:34.740
Don't be silly, Mary.

03:35.400 --> 03:37.640
You can't go to the shops now.

03:37.640 --> 03:40.020
He is a famous man.

03:40.940 --> 03:45.240
Do you understand an important person?

03:46.200 --> 03:47.480
Tony Maddock.

03:48.200 --> 03:49.420
I don't know him.

03:50.400 --> 03:51.700
Is he very rich?

03:52.700 --> 03:55.700
I don't know, Mary, but he's very important.

03:56.520 --> 03:57.360
I know that.

03:57.740 --> 03:58.540
Yes.

03:59.360 --> 04:01.600
Well, I'm going to the shops now.

04:02.460 --> 04:03.740
See you later, George.

04:03.740 --> 04:06.820
But, Mary, stop!

04:16.280 --> 04:17.420
Sing two.

04:18.140 --> 04:19.540
Fish for dinner.

04:22.660 --> 04:23.720
In the kitchen.

04:28.080 --> 04:31.320
Good morning, Judy.

04:32.200 --> 04:33.860
We've got good news.

04:34.660 --> 04:36.740
Tony Maddock is coming today.

04:37.540 --> 04:38.880
The famous TV star.

04:39.500 --> 04:40.380
Tony Ho.

04:41.160 --> 04:42.740
I don't think I know the name.

04:43.460 --> 04:44.500
I don't like TV.

04:45.220 --> 04:45.940
I like reading.

04:47.240 --> 04:48.680
Tony Maddock.

04:49.140 --> 04:49.860
That's right.

04:50.460 --> 04:51.540
Tony Maddock.

04:51.880 --> 04:54.200
Now, what have you got for dinner?

04:55.100 --> 04:56.740
Have you got any fish?

04:57.520 --> 04:59.860
He likes fish, his secretary says?

04:59.860 --> 05:02.900
No, I haven't got any fish today, Mr.

05:03.200 --> 05:03.300
Harris.

05:03.860 --> 05:05.480
Sorry, I've got some chicken.

05:06.180 --> 05:08.460
No, he wants fish.

05:09.400 --> 05:10.760
Can you buy some?

05:11.160 --> 05:12.760
Oh, no, Mr. Harris.

05:13.220 --> 05:15.240
I never buy fish on Thursdays.

05:15.680 --> 05:17.120
I always buy chicken.

05:17.760 --> 05:21.400
Well, his secretary says fish, not chicken.

05:22.000 --> 05:22.300
Right?

05:22.960 --> 05:24.340
Don't shout at me.

05:24.760 --> 05:25.880
I don't like it.

05:26.360 --> 05:27.080
I'm leaving.

05:27.080 --> 05:29.160
I'm not going to buy anything.

05:29.820 --> 05:30.560
I'm going home.

05:31.260 --> 05:34.860
No, Judy, please stop.

05:35.760 --> 05:37.280
I'm sorry, Judy.

05:37.940 --> 05:40.080
You're a good cook, Judy.

05:40.520 --> 05:41.960
A beautiful cook.

05:42.620 --> 05:44.400
Please don't leave now.

05:45.460 --> 05:47.940
Mr. Maddock is coming here today.

05:48.420 --> 05:49.760
And he wants fish.

05:50.520 --> 05:53.840
Please, please, please, please, Judy.

05:54.380 --> 05:56.220
Go and buy some nice fish.

05:57.220 --> 06:00.660
No, it's chicken on Thursdays.

06:01.100 --> 06:01.480
Right?

06:02.140 --> 06:04.500
Oh, okay, Judy.

06:05.500 --> 06:06.280
Chicken.

06:18.160 --> 06:19.320
Scene three.

06:24.080 --> 06:25.100
In the garden.

06:33.820 --> 06:35.320
Hello, Mr. Harris.

06:36.340 --> 06:38.520
You don't usually come into the garden.

06:39.500 --> 06:40.480
Can I help you?

06:41.360 --> 06:42.240
Hello, Peter.

06:43.180 --> 06:46.060
I need some flowers for our best room.

06:47.000 --> 06:49.940
Well, ten hours on the telephone.

06:50.560 --> 06:51.560
That's a long time.

06:52.000 --> 06:53.280
And expensive, too.

06:53.680 --> 06:54.660
No, Peter.

06:55.400 --> 06:56.860
Not ten hours.

06:57.420 --> 07:03.140
I want some flowers for our best room.

07:03.860 --> 07:04.680
Okay, okay.

07:05.620 --> 07:06.880
Don't shout, Mr. Harris.

07:07.220 --> 07:08.020
I'm going to hear you.

07:08.580 --> 07:09.240
Flowers.

07:09.960 --> 07:11.440
I've got lots of flowers.

07:12.140 --> 07:12.920
Thanks, Peter.

07:12.920 --> 07:16.200
Therefore an important TV star.

07:16.700 --> 07:18.400
He's coming here today.

07:19.240 --> 07:20.260
What's that?

07:20.880 --> 07:22.380
Your green car?

07:23.320 --> 07:24.340
No, Peter.

07:25.180 --> 07:25.320
No.

07:26.320 --> 07:30.440
A TV star here today.

07:31.220 --> 07:32.480
Okay, Mr. Harris.

07:32.900 --> 07:33.360
Don't shout.

07:34.020 --> 07:34.660
Don't shout.

07:35.420 --> 07:36.200
I can hear you.

07:47.220 --> 07:48.320
Scene four.

07:49.260 --> 07:50.760
The new light for Tony's room.

07:53.760 --> 07:54.780
In the corridor.

07:58.440 --> 08:01.020
Mary, can you help me?

08:01.740 --> 08:04.180
Take these flowers to Tony's room, please.

08:05.120 --> 08:07.320
I've got this new light for the room.

08:08.480 --> 08:09.220
Do you like it?

08:10.140 --> 08:12.060
The new light is green.

08:12.060 --> 08:15.300
It has yellow and red flowers on it.

08:16.380 --> 08:17.580
Oh, George.

08:18.840 --> 08:20.020
It's horrible.

08:21.100 --> 08:23.000
You can't put that in his room.

08:23.440 --> 08:24.420
Yes, I can.

08:25.020 --> 08:26.520
I think it's beautiful.

08:27.380 --> 08:30.220
I like it and I'm going to put

08:30.220 --> 08:30.760
it up now.

08:31.520 --> 08:32.400
Can you help me?

08:33.160 --> 08:35.260
Oh, all right.

08:36.220 --> 08:37.120
Give me the flowers.

08:42.810 --> 08:43.660
In the room.

08:46.540 --> 08:48.200
Hold the ladder, Mary.

08:48.980 --> 08:50.600
I'm going to put the light up.

08:51.320 --> 08:52.400
Careful now.

08:53.020 --> 08:54.820
I want a cup of coffee.

08:55.580 --> 08:56.880
Please, Mary.

08:57.480 --> 08:58.260
Not now.

08:59.220 --> 09:00.800
Hold the ladder for me.

09:01.660 --> 09:02.440
Careful.

09:03.940 --> 09:04.720
There.

09:05.740 --> 09:06.520
Ouch!

09:07.200 --> 09:09.640
You're standing on my hand.

09:09.640 --> 09:12.100
Hold the ladder, Mary.

09:12.760 --> 09:13.680
Don't go.

09:14.600 --> 09:15.200
Mary.

09:16.320 --> 09:17.060
Help!

09:20.300 --> 09:22.220
He falls off the ladder.

09:23.220 --> 09:24.320
Ooh.

09:25.500 --> 09:27.400
My head.

09:36.240 --> 09:37.400
Scene five.

09:38.080 --> 09:39.540
An old woman arrives.

09:43.820 --> 09:45.900
It is five o'clock.

09:46.660 --> 09:48.320
A woman is getting out of the taxi.

09:56.260 --> 09:57.620
Good afternoon.

09:58.280 --> 09:59.400
Are you the manager?

10:00.180 --> 10:00.720
No.

10:01.760 --> 10:02.440
Yes.

10:03.160 --> 10:04.340
Yes, I am.

10:04.960 --> 10:07.020
Have you got a room here for me?

10:07.660 --> 10:08.140
A room?

10:08.980 --> 10:09.780
Oh, no.

10:10.680 --> 10:11.740
I'm afraid we're full.

10:12.420 --> 10:14.360
We are very busy this year.

10:14.760 --> 10:15.080
What?

10:15.080 --> 10:16.400
No rooms.

10:17.080 --> 10:17.720
Busy.

10:18.360 --> 10:19.620
But I think my city...

10:19.620 --> 10:20.080
That's right.

10:20.620 --> 10:21.400
No rooms.

10:22.120 --> 10:24.920
We've got important people in the hotel today.

10:25.540 --> 10:28.180
But what's your name?

10:28.780 --> 10:29.820
Margaret Adams.

10:30.860 --> 10:32.120
And I'm tired, too.

10:32.620 --> 10:33.760
Oh, all right.

10:34.280 --> 10:34.920
Come in.

10:38.520 --> 10:40.240
In the hotel again.

10:42.980 --> 10:45.700
Yes, you can have a room for one

10:45.700 --> 10:46.860
or two nights.

10:47.740 --> 10:50.700
But it's small and you can't see the

10:50.700 --> 10:50.940
sea.

10:51.400 --> 10:53.160
But I want to see the sea.

10:53.840 --> 10:55.440
Have you got any other rooms?

10:56.180 --> 10:57.040
I don't know.

10:59.240 --> 10:59.920
No.

11:00.760 --> 11:02.320
There isn't another room.

11:03.080 --> 11:04.800
We're very busy, you see.

11:05.280 --> 11:06.540
And I'm very tired.

11:07.540 --> 11:10.080
The small room's okay.

11:11.120 --> 11:12.940
Why are you busy?

11:13.580 --> 11:16.020
A famous TV star is coming.

11:16.460 --> 11:18.540
Oh, very interesting.

11:19.700 --> 11:20.920
Do you like TV?

11:21.560 --> 11:21.980
No.

11:23.540 --> 11:24.420
Yes.

11:25.080 --> 11:26.140
Very much.

11:26.820 --> 11:28.160
Yes, I do, too.

11:29.060 --> 11:30.340
I like film's best.

11:33.220 --> 11:34.420
She laughs.

11:36.460 --> 11:37.660
Here's your key.

11:38.540 --> 11:40.500
Your room is number five.

11:40.860 --> 11:41.540
Thank you.

11:42.120 --> 11:44.200
I'm going up to my room now.

11:44.660 --> 11:45.980
Please bring my bag.

11:46.380 --> 11:47.940
It's outside in the street.

11:49.480 --> 11:51.160
The woman goes out.

11:52.100 --> 11:53.300
A bag?

11:54.440 --> 11:55.780
I haven't got time.

11:56.340 --> 11:58.880
I can't take her back to her room.

12:02.500 --> 12:06.020
George carries the woman's bag into the hotel

12:06.020 --> 12:08.420
and quickly puts it in a cupboard.

12:09.340 --> 12:10.740
Mary comes in.

12:11.580 --> 12:12.740
She is drinking coffee.

12:14.440 --> 12:16.180
Who's that woman, George?

12:17.140 --> 12:20.440
That's Miss Adams.

12:21.640 --> 12:22.640
She's in room five.

12:23.180 --> 12:25.360
Oh, that's a horrible room.

12:26.360 --> 12:27.220
It's very small.

12:27.220 --> 12:29.680
And you can't see the sea.

12:31.180 --> 12:32.060
That's right.

12:32.640 --> 12:33.780
But it is quiet.

12:34.540 --> 12:35.820
It's fine for her.

12:36.500 --> 12:39.080
She's only going to stay for one or

12:39.080 --> 12:39.680
two nights.

12:40.840 --> 12:43.160
Do you like the new light in the

12:43.160 --> 12:43.620
big room?

12:44.080 --> 12:45.880
It's nice, I think.

12:46.700 --> 12:47.780
Very nice.

12:48.500 --> 12:49.700
It's horrible, George.

12:51.080 --> 12:52.160
Red and yellow flowers.

12:53.040 --> 12:54.980
And it's very big.

12:55.700 --> 12:56.720
Is it safe?

12:57.360 --> 12:57.860
Safe?

12:58.800 --> 12:59.360
Yes.

13:00.060 --> 13:02.000
Oh, yes, it's safe.

13:31.900 --> 13:33.140
Scene six.

13:34.200 --> 13:35.320
The TV star.

13:39.280 --> 13:41.100
It is half past five.

13:42.040 --> 13:44.300
A young man is coming into the hotel

13:44.300 --> 13:45.720
carrying a small bag.

13:46.760 --> 13:47.700
He is wearing jeans.

13:49.480 --> 13:52.680
Oh, hello, hello.

13:52.680 --> 13:53.060
Hello.

13:53.640 --> 13:54.400
Welcome.

13:54.860 --> 13:55.180
Hello.

13:55.760 --> 13:56.620
Thank you.

13:57.080 --> 13:57.760
Thank you.

13:58.360 --> 13:59.020
Thank you.

13:59.780 --> 14:01.600
He takes the man's hand.

14:02.700 --> 14:03.740
That's okay.

14:05.200 --> 14:05.960
Why?

14:06.760 --> 14:08.180
You've got the big room.

14:08.820 --> 14:10.820
And there's a new light in there for

14:10.820 --> 14:11.260
you too.

14:11.940 --> 14:13.800
A beautiful new light.

14:14.640 --> 14:15.220
Very nice.

14:16.180 --> 14:17.140
Thank you very much.

14:17.800 --> 14:19.440
But I don't understand.

14:20.380 --> 14:22.060
Well, you're famous.

14:22.900 --> 14:24.860
You're a TV star.

14:25.560 --> 14:25.880
Me?

14:26.740 --> 14:27.080
Famous.

14:28.140 --> 14:29.200
A TV star.

14:30.720 --> 14:31.660
He laughs.

14:32.660 --> 14:34.640
And here's the key to your room.

14:35.500 --> 14:36.760
I can take your bag.

14:37.600 --> 14:38.780
Oh, thank you.

14:38.980 --> 14:40.020
But it's not heavy.

14:40.680 --> 14:41.640
I can carry it.

14:42.300 --> 14:43.660
And I'm not famous.

14:44.400 --> 14:45.820
Yes, you are.

14:46.440 --> 14:47.500
But I'm not.

14:48.290 --> 14:50.920
Ah, I see.

14:51.580 --> 14:53.820
You're not famous.

14:55.040 --> 14:58.140
You don't want any TV cameras here.

14:58.660 --> 15:01.540
Yes, I understand.

15:02.480 --> 15:03.140
You understand.

15:04.060 --> 15:04.420
Yes.

15:05.280 --> 15:07.940
You want a quiet holiday.

15:08.560 --> 15:11.080
You're not famous.

15:11.900 --> 15:13.660
All right.

15:13.980 --> 15:14.840
I understand.

15:15.700 --> 15:16.080
Good.

15:16.080 --> 15:19.360
Can I see the sea from my room?

15:20.340 --> 15:21.100
Oh, yes.

15:21.920 --> 15:23.980
It's one of the rooms in the front

15:23.980 --> 15:24.780
of the hotel.

15:25.560 --> 15:26.520
It's very nice.

15:28.000 --> 15:29.460
Is it expensive?

15:30.540 --> 15:32.420
I haven't got a lot of money, you

15:32.420 --> 15:32.580
know.

15:33.060 --> 15:33.860
That's okay.

15:34.800 --> 15:35.920
I like you.

15:36.320 --> 15:38.100
I don't need the money.

15:38.840 --> 15:40.860
For you, the room is free.

15:41.940 --> 15:42.980
I don't understand.

15:43.780 --> 15:44.580
Mary.

15:45.560 --> 15:46.220
Mary.

15:47.400 --> 15:48.040
Come here.

15:48.820 --> 15:51.100
Come and meet Mr. Maddock.

15:52.920 --> 15:54.500
Mary comes in.

15:55.120 --> 15:56.820
She's holding a cup of coffee.

15:57.500 --> 15:59.000
What do you want now?

15:59.560 --> 16:00.100
Mary.

16:00.720 --> 16:02.860
Meet Mr. Maddock.

16:03.560 --> 16:05.620
This is my wife, Mary.

16:06.560 --> 16:08.380
George takes Mary's arm.

16:09.240 --> 16:11.460
Her coffee goes over the young man's jeans.

16:12.460 --> 16:15.760
Oh, I'm very sorry.

16:16.240 --> 16:16.820
Your jeans.

16:17.500 --> 16:18.980
I'm sorry, Mr.

16:20.240 --> 16:21.340
Mr. Brown.

16:21.720 --> 16:22.520
Paul Brown.

16:23.100 --> 16:25.160
I'm sorry, Mr. Maddock.

16:25.580 --> 16:27.320
Please excuse my wife.

16:28.060 --> 16:30.320
We can clean your jeans for you here.

16:30.840 --> 16:32.100
I'm very sorry.

16:32.540 --> 16:34.000
Oh, it's all right.

16:34.620 --> 16:35.640
It isn't important.

16:36.340 --> 16:37.500
I can wash my jeans.

16:37.840 --> 16:39.520
I'm sorry, Mr. Brown.

16:40.300 --> 16:41.760
Don't be silly, Mary.

16:42.280 --> 16:44.980
His name is Mr. Maddock.

16:45.300 --> 16:46.300
Er, no.

16:46.800 --> 16:48.140
My name is Paul Brown.

16:48.700 --> 16:49.840
Yes, Mary.

16:50.400 --> 16:53.740
In this hotel, his name is Paul Brown.

16:54.380 --> 16:58.340
But on TV, his name is Tony Maddock.

16:58.920 --> 16:59.560
You understand?

17:00.480 --> 17:02.140
He wants a quiet holiday.

17:02.820 --> 17:04.740
He smiles at the young man.

17:05.420 --> 17:05.780
What?

17:06.440 --> 17:10.160
Mary, please ask Peter to take Mr. Brown's

17:10.160 --> 17:12.660
bag to his room quickly now.

17:13.340 --> 17:13.940
Thank you.

17:14.120 --> 17:16.000
Can I get another cup of coffee?

17:16.540 --> 17:18.060
No, Mary, you can't.

17:18.620 --> 17:19.580
The bag, Mary.

17:22.480 --> 17:25.780
Do you like flowers, Mr. Brown?

17:26.420 --> 17:29.080
You've got some nice flowers in your room.

17:30.120 --> 17:32.120
Yeah, from our garden, you know.

17:32.120 --> 17:33.540
Oh, no.

17:34.180 --> 17:34.580
I'm sorry.

17:34.840 --> 17:36.600
I don't like flowers very much.

17:37.870 --> 17:38.920
Fine, fine.

17:40.140 --> 17:42.240
I don't like flowers either.

17:43.340 --> 17:46.460
Mary, put the flowers in the kitchen, please.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.720
But Peter's going to be very angry, George.

17:50.440 --> 17:52.380
In the kitchen, Mary.

17:54.300 --> 17:56.660
Mary and the young man go out.

17:57.360 --> 17:58.520
The woman comes in.

18:00.160 --> 18:02.740
Excuse me, but where's my bag?

18:03.220 --> 18:03.800
What?

18:04.640 --> 18:06.420
Oh, your bag.

18:07.540 --> 18:08.180
It's here.

18:08.620 --> 18:10.180
I need it in my room.

18:10.880 --> 18:12.160
Yes, yes.

18:12.640 --> 18:13.480
I'm sorry, Mrs.

18:15.200 --> 18:16.540
But not now.

18:17.060 --> 18:19.320
I am going to take it to your

18:19.320 --> 18:21.580
room, but I'm very busy now.

18:22.280 --> 18:25.540
We have a very important person in the

18:25.540 --> 18:25.980
hotel.

18:25.980 --> 18:28.640
But my glasses are in the bag.

18:29.340 --> 18:31.500
I can't learn the new plea without my

18:31.500 --> 18:32.000
glasses.

18:32.440 --> 18:33.200
Sorry, Mrs.

18:34.900 --> 18:36.280
Not now.

18:38.640 --> 18:40.420
The young man comes in again.

18:41.840 --> 18:44.660
Mr. Brown, there you are.

18:45.340 --> 18:48.380
Is the room okay, Mr. Brown?

18:49.120 --> 18:50.420
Yes, it's fine.

18:50.720 --> 18:51.020
Thank you.

18:51.380 --> 18:52.240
Good, good.

18:53.000 --> 18:54.100
Would you like anything?

18:54.100 --> 18:55.320
A drink?

18:55.900 --> 18:56.420
Some champagne?

18:57.460 --> 18:58.120
A television?

18:58.880 --> 19:00.640
No, nothing, thank you.

19:00.940 --> 19:02.460
Please have a drink.

19:03.400 --> 19:06.080
Mary, bring a bottle of champagne.

19:07.220 --> 19:08.640
Mary comes in.

19:09.760 --> 19:11.100
Champagne, George?

19:11.700 --> 19:15.200
Yes, bring a bottle of champagne and ask

19:15.200 --> 19:18.580
Peter to put the television in Mr. Brown's

19:18.580 --> 19:18.780
room.

19:19.620 --> 19:22.700
But I don't like television and I don't

19:22.700 --> 19:23.280
drink champagne.

19:23.280 --> 19:24.400
Thank you very much.

19:24.840 --> 19:26.440
He doesn't want them, George.

19:27.640 --> 19:29.620
I'm going out for a walk near the

19:29.620 --> 19:30.160
sea now.

19:30.880 --> 19:31.840
What time is dinner?

19:32.480 --> 19:35.040
Dinner's at half past seven, Mr. Brown.

19:35.840 --> 19:38.980
Mary, go to the kitchen and talk to

19:38.980 --> 19:40.700
Judy about dinner, please.

19:41.160 --> 19:42.580
Don't shout, George.

19:42.920 --> 19:43.520
I'm going.

19:46.360 --> 19:47.900
Mary goes to the kitchen.

19:48.860 --> 19:50.080
The young man goes out.

19:51.000 --> 19:52.660
George goes back to reception.

19:54.040 --> 19:56.680
My bag, please, Mr. Harris.

19:57.400 --> 19:58.320
Ah, yes.

19:59.100 --> 20:00.460
It's here in the cupboard.

20:00.980 --> 20:02.820
You can take it to your room now.

20:03.120 --> 20:05.000
But I can't carry the bag.

20:05.620 --> 20:08.880
It's very heavy and I'm 74 years old.

20:09.440 --> 20:10.660
Oh, all right.

20:11.600 --> 20:12.180
Give it to me.

20:13.120 --> 20:15.400
He goes to the cupboard and takes out

20:15.400 --> 20:15.860
her bag.

20:16.760 --> 20:17.520
They go out.

20:25.260 --> 20:28.820
Scene seven, I don't like champagne.

20:35.640 --> 20:40.060
In the hotel's restaurant, it is after eight

20:40.060 --> 20:40.620
o'clock.

20:41.340 --> 20:43.600
George is looking at a picture on the

20:43.600 --> 20:43.900
wall.

20:44.820 --> 20:47.200
The old woman is sitting at a table.

20:48.420 --> 20:49.760
Mr. Harris.

20:50.360 --> 20:50.820
Yes?

20:51.420 --> 20:53.320
I'd like my dinner now, please.

20:54.080 --> 20:56.380
It's ten minutes past eight now, you know.

20:56.740 --> 20:58.120
Oh, I'm sorry.

20:58.860 --> 21:00.060
We're very busy today.

21:00.660 --> 21:01.880
What would you like?

21:02.280 --> 21:03.440
I'd like some fish.

21:04.080 --> 21:05.400
I'm sorry, Mrs.

21:07.220 --> 21:09.120
We haven't got any fish.

21:09.720 --> 21:12.520
No, there isn't any fish.

21:13.480 --> 21:14.120
Oh, well.

21:15.040 --> 21:16.600
What about a pizza?

21:17.360 --> 21:19.380
There's pizza here on the menu.

21:20.080 --> 21:20.680
Sorry.

21:21.120 --> 21:22.660
There's no pizza today.

21:23.280 --> 21:24.160
No pizza.

21:25.340 --> 21:26.940
Well, what have you got?

21:27.580 --> 21:28.180
Chicken.

21:28.780 --> 21:29.780
We've got chicken.

21:30.440 --> 21:31.180
All right.

21:31.880 --> 21:33.480
I'd like some chicken, please.

21:35.560 --> 21:37.340
George is not listening.

21:38.180 --> 21:40.600
The young man is coming into the restaurant.

21:41.600 --> 21:43.760
George goes to Mr. Brown's table.

21:45.040 --> 21:47.400
Hello, Mr. Brown.

21:48.200 --> 21:49.300
Here's your table.

21:50.080 --> 21:52.080
Mr. Brown sits down.

21:52.800 --> 21:53.960
Can I help you?

21:54.600 --> 21:56.260
What can I get for you?

21:58.080 --> 22:01.840
I'd like some chicken, please, Mr. Harris.

22:02.360 --> 22:03.400
All right, Mrs.

22:04.560 --> 22:05.680
All right.

22:06.320 --> 22:06.780
Don't shout.

22:07.520 --> 22:09.040
I'm sorry, Mr.

22:09.040 --> 22:11.860
I'd like a glass champagne, Mr. Brown.

22:12.500 --> 22:14.780
Would you like some champagne now?

22:15.320 --> 22:16.240
It's free.

22:16.900 --> 22:17.660
No, thanks.

22:17.920 --> 22:19.120
A glass of water, please.

22:19.760 --> 22:21.340
Please have some champagne.

22:21.920 --> 22:22.860
No, no.

22:23.220 --> 22:24.180
I don't like champagne.

22:24.600 --> 22:27.480
I'd like a glass of water, please.

22:29.260 --> 22:31.620
George goes to the woman's table.

22:32.400 --> 22:33.180
He is angry.

22:34.240 --> 22:34.520
Mrs.

22:35.120 --> 22:36.860
My name is Adams.

22:36.860 --> 22:38.520
Miss Adams.

22:39.180 --> 22:40.140
Miss Adams.

22:41.060 --> 22:43.600
We have a famous TV star here.

22:44.040 --> 22:45.380
And we're very busy.

22:46.180 --> 22:47.360
I can't do everything.

22:48.320 --> 22:49.900
Do you understand that?

22:50.200 --> 22:50.860
Oh, yes.

22:51.480 --> 22:52.060
I understand.

22:53.080 --> 22:54.800
I am a TV star.

22:55.740 --> 22:56.180
Who?

22:57.120 --> 22:57.700
What?

22:58.600 --> 23:00.940
You're a TV star.

23:01.460 --> 23:02.040
That's right.

23:02.740 --> 23:04.820
My name is Tony Maddock.

23:04.820 --> 23:08.580
But Tony Maddock is a man.

23:09.340 --> 23:09.920
Oh, no.

23:10.700 --> 23:12.920
Tony is a woman's name, too.

23:13.700 --> 23:16.260
T-O-N-I.

23:16.800 --> 23:19.160
My real name is Margaret Adams.

23:19.940 --> 23:23.080
But on TV, my name is Tony Maddock.

23:24.280 --> 23:25.080
What?

23:26.080 --> 23:27.240
Oh, no.

23:28.040 --> 23:29.540
Yes, Mr. Harris.

23:30.140 --> 23:33.120
And now I'm going to leave this hotel,

23:33.120 --> 23:35.940
the Happy Holiday Hotel.

23:36.740 --> 23:39.800
I don't know about happy, but I know

23:39.800 --> 23:40.740
it isn't good.

23:41.400 --> 23:43.360
And I'm not happy here.

23:43.980 --> 23:45.520
I've got a small room.

23:46.200 --> 23:47.600
I can't see the sea.

23:48.540 --> 23:52.120
And, Mr. Harris, you're a very silly man.

23:53.940 --> 23:56.280
Tony Maddock goes out of the restaurant.

23:57.400 --> 23:59.760
George looks at the young man sadly.

24:00.760 --> 24:02.980
And who are you?

24:03.660 --> 24:05.040
I'm Paul Brown.

24:05.860 --> 24:07.780
You're not the TV star.

24:08.460 --> 24:09.940
No, Mr. Harris.

24:10.840 --> 24:11.620
I'm a student.

24:12.320 --> 24:13.420
A student?

24:15.700 --> 24:17.140
He runs to the door.

24:18.320 --> 24:22.980
Miss Maddock, Miss Maddock, please don't leave.

24:23.920 --> 24:25.840
Have some champagne, please.

24:26.960 --> 24:27.660
It's free.

24:45.960 --> 24:49.340
In the corridor, outside the big room,

24:50.140 --> 24:52.140
the woman is talking to Mary.

24:53.360 --> 24:55.020
Mary has got the woman's bag.

24:56.380 --> 24:57.860
I'm very sorry.

24:58.680 --> 24:59.740
George is the only one.

24:59.740 --> 25:00.460
It's silly sometimes.

25:01.460 --> 25:03.880
We can move you to the big room.

25:04.720 --> 25:06.720
And the young man can have the other

25:06.720 --> 25:07.140
room.

25:07.840 --> 25:09.640
Please don't leave now.

25:11.480 --> 25:14.440
In the big room, Mary and Tony Maddock

25:14.440 --> 25:16.040
are looking out of the window.

25:17.300 --> 25:18.960
George runs into the room.

25:20.540 --> 25:22.340
Miss Maddock, here you are.

25:23.140 --> 25:23.940
Please stay.

25:24.800 --> 25:26.660
You can have the room for nothing.

25:27.370 --> 25:27.780
Free.

25:28.460 --> 25:30.040
He takes her arm.

25:30.560 --> 25:31.920
No, I'm sorry.

25:32.500 --> 25:33.860
Goodbye, Mr. Harris.

25:35.510 --> 25:37.980
She is standing under the new lamp.

25:39.470 --> 25:41.660
Suddenly the lamp begins to fall.

25:42.500 --> 25:44.780
George, stop.

25:46.040 --> 25:46.640
Listen.

25:47.200 --> 25:47.700
Oh!

25:49.360 --> 25:50.300
Dad!

25:54.360 --> 25:56.060
George pushes the woman.

25:56.920 --> 25:58.020
She falls over.

25:59.000 --> 26:00.660
George falls on top of her.

26:01.540 --> 26:03.540
The lamp falls on George's head.

26:04.200 --> 26:06.760
He lies there and doesn't move.

26:07.860 --> 26:11.660
Miss Maddock, are you all right?

26:13.220 --> 26:14.660
I'm fine.

26:15.660 --> 26:16.720
She gets up.

26:17.500 --> 26:19.800
But how is Mr. Harris?

26:20.700 --> 26:21.560
George?

26:22.780 --> 26:23.660
George.

26:24.800 --> 26:26.680
Speak to me, George.

26:27.760 --> 26:29.300
Oh, Mr. Harris.

26:29.980 --> 26:31.200
Are you all right?

26:32.340 --> 26:33.360
They look at George.

26:34.300 --> 26:36.020
He doesn't speak or move.

26:36.860 --> 26:40.180
That horrible light isn't safe.

26:41.180 --> 26:45.180
Oh, George, can you hear me?

26:46.040 --> 26:48.500
Please say something, George.

26:49.340 --> 26:50.840
Now I understand.

26:52.020 --> 26:56.520
That lamp nearly, and Mr. Harris...

26:57.180 --> 26:59.520
Oh, what a nice man.

27:00.380 --> 27:03.460
Because of Mr. Harris, I'm safe.

27:04.680 --> 27:07.060
Thank you, Mr. Harris.

27:07.800 --> 27:10.560
Thank you, George.

27:12.760 --> 27:13.500
Champagne.

27:15.280 --> 27:17.100
What a nice man.

27:17.900 --> 27:19.780
Thank you, Mrs. Harris.

27:20.680 --> 27:21.780
Don't thank me.

27:22.480 --> 27:23.940
Thanks, Silio, George.

27:25.240 --> 27:27.800
Would you like a glass of champagne now,

27:28.040 --> 27:28.660
Miss Maddock?

27:30.120 --> 27:31.360
They go out.

27:32.000 --> 27:34.000
George is lying on the floor.

27:34.000 --> 27:36.680
He slowly opens one eye.

27:37.920 --> 27:39.800
He's very...

27:39.800 --> 27:45.280
No, she's very, very famous.

27:46.040 --> 27:48.580
She's a star.

